@startuml
title Google SSO Authentication Flow (/talent/google)
actor User
participant "Frontend (SPA)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(/auth/talent/google)" as BE
participant "Google Identity\nServices" as Google
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

== Authentication Step ==
User -> FE: Click "Login with Google"\nor "Sign in with Google"
activate FE
FE -> Google: Request ID Token (popup/redirect)
activate Google
Google -> User: Show Consent Screen
User -> Google: Approve Access
Google -> FE: Return **id_token** (JWT)
deactivate Google

== Verification Step ==
FE -> BE: POST /auth/talent/google\n{ "id_token": "..." }
activate BE
BE -> Google: verify_oauth2_token(id_token)
activate Google
Google -> BE: Token Payload\n(email, name, sub, picture)
deactivate Google

alt Token Invalid
    BE -> FE: 401 Unauthorized / Invalid Token
    FE -> User: Show Error Message
end

== Registration / Login Logic ==
BE -> DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?
activate DB
DB -> BE: User Record OR Null
deactivate DB

alt User Not Found (Registration)
    BE -> DB: INSERT INTO users (email, name, role='candidate')
    activate DB
    DB -> BE: New User ID
    deactivate DB
    BE -> DB: INSERT INTO candidate_info (user_id, cv_url=None)
    activate DB
    DB -> BE: Success
    deactivate DB
    note right of BE: Matches behavior in `Authenticator.google_authenticate_talent`
else User Exists
    alt Role != 'candidate'
        BE -> FE: Error: Role Mismatch
    end
end

== Token Generation ==
BE -> BE: create_access_token()\ncreate_refresh_token()
BE -> FE: Returns **LoginResponse**\n{ access_token, refresh_token, user: {...} }
deactivate BE

FE -> FE: Store Tokens (LocalStorage/Cookie)
FE -> User: Redirect to Dashboard
deactivate FE
@enduml
